    <name>
      <text>Applying logarithms to roots</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>
A square plot of land in <strong>Konzaa city</strong> has an area of \(\sqrt{{@base@}}\) hectares. By applying logarithms, write \(\sqrt{{@base@}}\) in terms of \(\log {@base@}\).
</p>

<p>
[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]
</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
First, rewrite the square root as a fractional index:
</p>

<p>
\[
\sqrt{{@base@}} = {@base@}^{1/2}
\]
</p>

<p>
Now apply the logarithm law:
</p>

<p>
\[
\log(a^n) = n\log a
\]
</p>

<p>
So,
</p>

<p>
\[
\log(\sqrt{{@base@}}) = \log({@base@}^{1/2}) = \frac{1}{2}\log {@base@}
\]
</p>

<p>
Therefore, the correct answer is:
</p>

<p>
\[
\boxed{\frac{1}{2}\log {@base@}}
\]
</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
